* Read from jira.url
* describe
** 'git jira describe all' will describe all branches in current repo (like CCMOC-224 and CCMOC-252)
** 'git jira describe mine' that only shows the current users issues
* list
** 'git jira list mine' to list only the current users issues
* git jira start <branch> should search from the existing issues and start from there
** Only if there isn't any matching one should it start a new one (and only after prompting)
* check that password is actually optional and will be prompted for otherwise
* Pretty print list of projects
* git jira switch will switch between open branches while showing their summaries.
